# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets — _redirects file
#
# This site is deployed as a Cloudflare Worker with the Static Assets
# binding (not Cloudflare Pages). The _redirects format is supported,
# but with one key restriction: **only relative URLs are allowed**.
# Cross-host redirects (e.g. www.example.com → example.com) cannot be
# expressed here — the build fails with code 10021 if absolute URLs
# appear. Use a Cloudflare zone-level Redirect Rule for cross-host
# redirects instead.
#
# URL canonicalization for this site is enforced at three layers:
#
#   1. wrangler.jsonc -> assets.html_handling = "drop-trailing-slash"
#      Worker auto-redirects /path/ -> /path. Supersedes any slash
#      rules we could write here — keeping this file mostly empty is
#      the right choice given that.
#
#   2. astro.config.mjs -> trailingSlash: 'never'
#      Astro generates dist/<page>.html (not dist/<page>/index.html)
#      so the canonical-form URLs match what the Worker serves.
#
#   3. BaseLayout.astro canonical tag
#      <link rel="canonical"> always derives from Astro.site
#      (https://perspectiv.net) + path, with trailing slash stripped.
#      Tells Google the canonical form regardless of what URL the
#      visitor hit.
#
#   4. Cloudflare zone Redirect Rules (separate, in the Cloudflare
#      dashboard — NOT in this repo):
#       - www.perspectiv.net/*  ->  301  ->  perspectiv.net/*
#
# Add page-level overrides below only when needed. Examples:
#   /old-blog-post   /blog/new-post   301
#   /legacy/*        /docs/:splat     301
